    "tag": "canvas",
    "description": "A full-screen plasma color field driven by layered sine wave functions. Mouse position dynamically shifts the plasma pattern. Click to invert the color phase. Fluid, hypnotic, and zero-dependency.",
    "previewCode": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n<title>Plasma Color Field</title>\n<style>*{margin:0;padding:0}body{overflow:hidden}canvas{display:block}.label{position:fixed;bottom:28px;left:50%;transform:translateX(-50%);color:rgba(255,255,255,.3);font:700 9px/1 sans-serif;letter-spacing:.4em;text-transform:uppercase}</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<canvas id=\"c\"></canvas>\n<div class=\"label\">Move mouse &bull; Click to invert</div>\n<script>\nvar c=document.getElementById('c'),ctx=c.getContext('2d');\nvar W=c.width=window.innerWidth,H=c.height=window.innerHeight;\nvar mx=0.5,my=0.5,inv=1,t=0;\nvar off=ctx.createImageData(W,H);\nwindow.addEventListener('mousemove',function(e){mx=e.clientX/W;my=e.clientY/H;});\nwindow.addEventListener('click',function(){inv*=-1;});\nwindow.addEventListener('resize',function(){W=c.width=window.innerWidth;H=c.height=window.innerHeight;off=ctx.createImageData(W,H);});\nfunction plasma(x,y,t){\n var v=Math.sin(x*8+t);\n v+=Math.sin(y*6-t*.7);\n v+=Math.sin((x+y)*5+t*.5);\n v+=Math.sin(Math.sqrt(x*x+y*y)*8-t*.8);\n v+=Math.sin(x*10*mx+t*.3);\n v+=Math.sin(y*10*my-t*.4);\n return v/6;\n}\nfunction draw(){\n requestAnimationFrame(draw);t+=0.018;\n var d=off.data,i=0;\n for(var py=0;py<H;py+=2){\n for(var px=0;px<W;px+=2){\n var v=plasma(px/W,py/H,t)*inv;\n var r=Math.sin(v*Math.PI)*127+128;\n var g=Math.sin(v*Math.PI+2.09)*127+128;\n var b=Math.sin(v*Math.PI+4.18)*127+128;\n var idx=(py*W+px)*4;\n d[idx]=r;d[idx+1]=g;d[idx+2]=b;d[idx+3]=255;\n if(px+1<W){d[idx+4]=r;d[idx+5]=g;d[idx+6]=b;d[idx+7]=255;}\n if(py+1<H){var idx2=((py+1)*W+px)*4;d[idx2]=r;d[idx2+1]=g;d[idx2+2]=b;d[idx2+3]=255;}\n }\n }\n ctx.putImageData(off,0,0);\n}\ndraw();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>",
    "code": "'use client';\nimport { useEffect, useRef } from 'react';\n\nexport const PlasmaColorField = () => {\n const canvasRef = useRef<HTMLCanvasElement>(null);\n\n useEffect(() => {\n const c = canvasRef.current!;\n const ctx = c.getContext('2d')!;\n let W = c.width = window.innerWidth, H = c.height = window.innerHeight;\n let mx = 0.5, my = 0.5, inv = 1, t = 0, raf: number;\n let off = ctx.createImageData(W, H);\n\n const plasma = (x: number, y: number, t: number) => {\n let v = Math.sin(x*8+t);\n v += Math.sin(y*6-t*.7);\n v += Math.sin((x+y)*5+t*.5);\n v += Math.sin(Math.sqrt(x*x+y*y)*8-t*.8);\n v += Math.sin(x*10*mx+t*.3);\n v += Math.sin(y*10*my-t*.4);\n return v / 6;\n };\n\n const onMove = (e: MouseEvent) => { mx = e.clientX/W; my = e.clientY/H; };\n const onClick = () => { inv *= -1; };\n const onResize = () => { W = c.width = window.innerWidth; H = c.height = window.innerHeight; off = ctx.createImageData(W,H); };\n window.addEventListener('mousemove', onMove);\n window.addEventListener('click', onClick);\n window.addEventListener('resize', onResize);\n\n const draw = () => {\n raf = requestAnimationFrame(draw); t += 0.018;\n const d = off.data;\n for (let py = 0; py < H; py += 2) {\n for (let px = 0; px < W; px += 2) {\n const v = plasma(px/W, py/H, t) * inv;\n const r = Math.sin(v*Math.PI)*127+128;\n const g = Math.sin(v*Math.PI+2.09)*127+128;\n const b = Math.sin(v*Math.PI+4.18)*127+128;\n const idx = (py*W+px)*4;\n d[idx]=r; d[idx+1]=g; d[idx+2]=b; d[idx+3]=255;\n if (px+1<W) { d[idx+4]=r; d[idx+5]=g; d[idx+6]=b; d[idx+7]=255; }\n if (py+1<H) { const i2=((py+1)*W+px)*4; d[i2]=r; d[i2+1]=g; d[i2+2]=b; d[i2+3]=255; }\n }\n }\n ctx.putImageData(off, 0, 0);\n };\n draw();\n return () => { cancelAnimationFrame(raf); window.removeEventListener('mousemove',onMove); window.removeEventListener('click',onClick); window.removeEventListener('resize',onResize); };\n }, []);\n\n return (\n <div className=\"relative w-full h-screen overflow-hidden\">\n <canvas ref={canvasRef} className=\"block w-full h-full\" />\n <p className=\"absolute bottom-7 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 text-white/30 text-[9px] font-bold tracking-[.4em] uppercase pointer-events-none\">\n Move mouse &bull; Click to invert\n </p>\n </div>\n );\n};",
    "prompt": "Create a full-screen plasma color field using canvas ImageData pixel manipulation. For each pixel compute a plasma value: sum of 6 sine waves with arguments involving x/W, y/H, time, and mouse position (mx, my). Map plasma value to RGB using sin(v*PI + phase) with phase offsets 0, 2.09, 4.18 for R, G, B channels. Render at half resolution (2x2 pixel blocks) for performance. Mouse position shifts 2 of the 6 sine wave arguments. Click inverts the plasma phase (multiply by -1). Animate at t += 0.018 per frame.",
    "likes": 0,
    "author": "Animation AI",
    "featured": true,
    "createdAt": "2026-05-10T13:19:37.565Z",
    "updatedAt": "2026-05-10T13:19:37.565Z"
